Sweet and Savory Chicken Stir Fry
  --Cook's Country

1 c pineapple juice
3 tbsp shoyu
3 tbsp sweet chili sauce
2 tbsp cornstarch
3 garlic cloves, minced
3x 6-8 oz boneless, skinless chicken breast, sliced crosswise 1/2" thick
1 tbsp vegetable oil
12 oz broccoli florets, cut into 1/2" pieces 
1 c 1" pineapple chunks
1/4 tsp salt
1/4 c water
1/4 c cilantro leaves

Whisk pineapple juice, soy sauce, chili sauce, cornstarch, and garlic in bowl until cornstarch is dissolved. Combine chicken and 3 tbsp pineapple juice mixture in second bowl and let sit for 15 min. Heat oil in 12" nonstick skillet over high heat until just smoking. Add chicken and cook, without stirring, until well browned on bottom, ~2 min. Stir and continue to cook until chicken is spotty brown and cooked through, ~2 min longer. Transfer chicken to large plate. Add broccoli, pineapple, and salt to now-empty skillet. Cover and cook over high heat, shaking skillet occasionally, until broccoli is tender, ~3 min. Return chicken to skillet. Add water and remaining pineapple juice mixture and cook until slightly thickened, ~1 min. Sprinkle with cilantro leaves and serve. Can be sered over rice, noodles, etc.
